 by supremacism. At the time, however, British civil imperial flying was presented romantically in books, magazines and exhibitions. Eighty years on, imperial flying is still remembered, reproduced and re-enacted in caricature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAeronautics, CommercialxSocial aspectszGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aAir travelxSocial aspectszGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aImperialismxSocial aspectszGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aTranscontinental flightsxSocial aspectszGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 4aStudies in Imperialism 2017. 7aTRANSPORTATION / Aviation / History.2bisacsh  aBritish imperial aviation.  aaerial adventure.  aairline passengers.  acommercial flying.  aimperial journeys.  aimperial passages.  aimperial plumage.  aprivate flying.  apublicity.  are-flying empire.  avirtual flying.1 aPirie, Gordon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611847940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526118479423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526118479/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles